Daud Olatunji, Abeokuta The Osile of Oke-Ona Egbaland, Oba Adedapo Tejuoso, has  urged the President, Major-General  Mohammadu Buhari (retd.) to declare a national day of prayer to combat the menace of coronavirus ravaging the country. Oba Tejuoso, a first class Oba in Ogun State,  made the call while commencing the distribution of food items as palliatives to his subjects at his residence in Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. The monarch who attributed the cause of coronavirus to the sins and stubbornness of the people, said for Nigeria to win the war against COVID-19,  Nigerians, irrespective of religious affiliations must dedicate a day for prayer nationwide to seek God’s face and intervention. The monarch who described the lockdown in the country as “imprisonment,” said  “only God can save us from this prison.” Speaking on the distribution of the food items, Oba Tejuoso disclosed that  20 bags of garri, 20 bags of rice, 14 bags of beans, three bags of salt and 25 cartoons of noodles to residents of 10 townships under Oke-Ona Egba had been provided. Copyright PUNCH.
